<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="141" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="141">
The protologue of 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Fimbristylis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Fimbristylis salbundia" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="salbundia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Fimbristylis salbundia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[≡ 
<taxonomicName authority="Lestiboudois, 1819" authorityName="Lestiboudois" authorityYear="1819" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Trichelostylis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trichelostylis salbundia" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="salbundia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Trichelostylis salbundia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
] was based on two collections of Wallich, i.e. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Wallich 3499</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">3526</emphasis>
from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="‘Nepalia’">'Nepalia'</normalizedToken>
and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="‘Silhet’">'Silhet'</normalizedToken>
, respectively (
<bibRefCitation author="Wallich, N" journalOrPublisher="East India Company, London" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/1480954" refId="B27" refString="Wallich, N, 1828. A Numerical list of Dried Specimens of Plants in the East India Company's Museum. East India Company, London, https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/1480954" title="A Numerical list of Dried Specimens of Plants in the East India Company's Museum." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/1480954" year="1828">Wallich 1828</bibRefCitation>
; Nees 1834). All collections representing 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">3499</emphasis>
were later annotated as 
<taxonomicName genus="F." lsidName="F. quinquangularis" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" rank="species" species="quinquangularis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">F. quinquangularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Vahl) Kunth., except 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">3499c</emphasis>
at B, which was 
<taxonomicName genus="F." lsidName="F. salbundia" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" rank="species" species="salbundia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">F. salbundia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nees) Kunth (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/4111856" author="Clarke, CB" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of Miscellaneous Information, (Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew)" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="264 - 281" refId="B2" refString="Clarke, CB, 1907. Reductions of the Wallichian Herbarium: III. Cyperaceae. Bulletin of Miscellaneous Information, (Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew) 7: 264 - 281, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/4111856" title="Reductions of the Wallichian Herbarium: III. Cyperaceae." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/4111856" volume="7" year="1907">Clarke 1907</bibRefCitation>
). The collection 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">3499c</emphasis>
at B was destroyed in 1943, during the Second World War (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3417/2015018" author="Halder, S" journalOrPublisher="Novon" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="354 - 361" refId="B12" refString="Halder, S, Dey, S, 2016. Typifications in the genus Fimbristylis (Cyperaceae), II. Novon 24 (4): 354 - 361, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3417/2015018" title="Typifications in the genus Fimbristylis (Cyperaceae), II." url="https://doi.org/10.3417/2015018" volume="24" year="2016">Halder and Dey 2016</bibRefCitation>
). Subsequently, the occurrence of 
<taxonomicName genus="F." lsidName="F. salbundia" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" rank="species" species="salbundia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">F. salbundia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was not reported in the published works (
<bibRefCitation author="Koyama, T" editor="Hara, H" journalOrPublisher="British Museum (Natural History), London" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" pagination="96 - 120" refId="B14" refString="Koyama, T, 1978. Cyperaceae. In: Hara, H, Stearn, WT, Williams, LHJ, Eds., An Enumeration of the Flowering Plants of Nepal 1. British Museum (Natural History), London: 96 - 120" title="Cyperaceae." volumeTitle="An Enumeration of the Flowering Plants of Nepal 1." year="1978">Koyama 1978</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Press, JR" journalOrPublisher="Edinburgh Journal of Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" refId="B19" refString="Press, JR, Shrestha, KK, Sutton, DA, 2000. Cyperaceae. Annotated Checklist of the Flowering Plants of Nepal. The Natural History Museum, London, 86-97." title="Cyperaceae. Annotated Checklist of the Flowering Plants of Nepal. The Natural History Museum, London, 86 - 97." year="2000">Press et al. 2000</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Rajbhandari, KR" journalOrPublisher="In: Jha PK, Siwakoti M, Rajbhandary S (Eds) Frontiers of Botany, Central Department of Botany, Tribhuvan University, Kathmandu, Nepal" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" refId="B22" refString="Rajbhandari, KR, Rai, SK, 2017. Cyperaceae. A Handbook of the Flowering Plants of Nepal 1. Department of Plant Resources, Kathmandu, Nepal, 206-261." title="Cyperaceae. A Handbook of the Flowering Plants of Nepal 1. Department of Plant Resources, Kathmandu, Nepal, 206 - 261." year="2017">Rajbhandari and Rai 2017</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Shrestha, KK" journalOrPublisher="Botanic Garden, Howrah" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" refId="B24" refString="Shrestha, KK, Bhattarai, S, Bhandari, P, 2018. Cyperaceae. Handbook of Flowering Plants of Nepal 1. Scientific Publishers, Jodhpur, India, 194-222." title="Cyperaceae. Handbook of Flowering Plants of Nepal 1. Scientific Publishers, Jodhpur, India, 194 - 222." year="2018">Shrestha et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="POWO" journalOrPublisher="Edinburgh Journal of Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" publicationUrl="http://www.plantsoftheworldonline.org/" refId="B18" refString="POWO, 2019. Plants of the World Online. Facilitated by the Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew. http://www.plantsoftheworldonline.org/" title="Plants of the World Online. Facilitated by the Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew." url="http://www.plantsoftheworldonline.org/" year="2019">POWO 2019</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Govaerts, R" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" publicationUrl="http://www.kew.org/wcsp/monocots/" refId="B11" refString="Govaerts, R, Simpson, DA, Goetghebeur, P, Wilson, KL, Egorova, T, Bruhl, JL, 2021. World Checklist of Cyperaceae. Kew: The Board of Trustees of the Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew. http://www.kew.org/wcsp/monocots/" title="World Checklist of Cyperaceae. Kew: The Board of Trustees of the Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew." url="http://www.kew.org/wcsp/monocots/" year="2021">Govaerts et al. 2021</bibRefCitation>
). The rediscovery of 
<taxonomicName genus="F." lsidName="F. salbundia" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" rank="species" species="salbundia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">F. salbundia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
after 200 years confirms the occurrence of this taxon in Nepal.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="141">
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Fimbristylis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Fimbristylis salbundia" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="salbundia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Fimbristylis salbundia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="F." lsidName="F. quinquangularis" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" rank="species" species="quinquangularis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">F. quinquangularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished, based on the nature of its leaf sheaths and achene character. 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Fimbristylis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Fimbristylis salbundia" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="salbundia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Fimbristylis salbundia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterised by the presence of bladeless sheaths and sparsely verruculose achene, surface pitted with more than nine vertical rows of transversely oblong epidermal cells. However, 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Fimbristylis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Fimbristylis quinquangularis" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="quinquangularis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="141">Fimbristylis quinquangularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has leaf sheaths with blades and densely verruculose achene with up to six vertical rows of transversely linear-oblong epidermal cells.
</paragraph>
